1.description: For some time after its birth, it grows by gaining nourishment from the seed on its back.

2.description: When the bud on its back starts swelling, a sweet aroma wafts to indicate the flower's coming bloom.

3.description: After a rainy day, the flower on its back smells stronger. The scent attracts other Pokémon.

4.description: From the time it is born, a flame burns at the tip of its tail. Its life would end if the flame were to go out.

5.description: When it swings its burning tail, it elevates the air temperature to unbearably high levels.

6.description: Its wings can carry this pokemon close to an altitude of 4,600 feet. It blows out fire at very high temperatures.

7.description: Shoots water at prey while in the water. Withdraws into its shell when in danger.

8.description: It is said to live 10,000 years. Its furry tail is popular as a symbol of longevity.

9.description: The pressurized water jets on this brutal Pokémon's shell are used for high-speed tackles.

10.description: Its feet have suction cups designed to stick to any surface. It tenaciously climbs trees to forage.

11.description: This Pokémon is vulnerable to attack while its shell is soft, exposing its weak and tender body.

12.description: The wings are protected by rain-repellent dust. As a result, this Pokémon can fly about even in rain.

13.description: Its poison stinger is very powerful. Its bright-colored body is intended to warn off its enemies.

14.description: While awaiting evolution, it hides from predators under leaves and in nooks of branches.

15.description: May appear in a swarm. Flies at violent speeds, all the while stabbing with the toxic stinger on its rear.

16.description: It is docile and prefers to avoid conflict. If disturbed, however, it can ferociously strike back.

17.description: Very protective of its sprawling territorial area, this Pokémon will fiercely peck at any intruder.

18.description: It spreads its gorgeous wings widely to intimidate enemies. It races through the skies at Mach-2 speed.

19.description: It searches for food all day. It gnaws on hard objects to wear down its fangs, which grow constantly during its lifetime.

20.description: With its long fangs, this surprisingly violent Pokémon can gnaw away even thick concrete with ease.

21.description: Eats bugs in grassy areas. It has to flap its short wings at high speed to stay airborne.

22.description: It has the stamina to fly all day on its broad wings. It fights by using its sharp beak.

23.description: Moving silently and stealthily, it eats the eggs of birds, such as Pidgey and Spearow, whole.

24.description: To intimidate foes, it spreads its chest wide and makes eerie sounds by expelling air from its mouth.

25.description: It has small electric sacs on both its cheeks. If threatened, it looses electric charges from the sacs.

26.description: It can loose 100,000-volt bursts of electricity, instantly downing foes several times its size.

27.description: Disliking water, it lives in deep burrows in arid areas. It can roll itself instantly into a ball.

28.description: Curls up into a spiny ball when threatened. It can roll while curled up to attack or escape.

29.description: Small and very docile, it protects itself with its small, poisonous horn when attacked.

30.description: When feeding its young, it first chews the food into a paste, then spits it out for the offspring.

31.description: The body is covered by stiff, needlelike scales. If it becomes excited, the needles bristle outwards.

32.description: Its large ears are flapped like wings when it is listening to distant sounds. It extends toxic barbs when angered.

33.description: An aggressive Pokémon that is quick to attack. The horn on its head secretes a powerful venom.

34.description: One swing of its mighty tail can snap a telephone pole as if it were a matchstick.

35.description: The moonlight that it stores in the wings on its back apparently gives it the ability to float in midair.

36.description: A timid fairy Pokémon that is rarely seen, it will run and hide the moment it senses people.

37.description: While young, it has six gorgeous tails. When it grows, several new tails are sprouted.

38.description: Very smart and very vengeful. Grabbing one of its many tails could result in a 1,000-year curse.

39.description: If it inflates to sing a lullaby, it can perform longer and cause sure drowsiness in its audience.

40.description: The body is soft and rubbery. When angered, it will suck in air and inflate itself to an enormous size.

41.description: It has no eyes. Instead, it relies on its ultrasonic cries for echolocation to flit about in darkness

42.description: Once it starts sucking blood, it does not stop until it is full. It flies at night in search of prey.

43.description: Its scientific name is 'Oddium Wanderus.' At night, it is said to walk nearly 1,000 feet on its two roots.

44.description: The honey it drools from its mouth smells so atrocious, it can curl noses more than a mile away.

45.description: It has the world's largest petals. With every step, the petals shake out heavy clouds of toxic pollen.

46.description: Burrows under the ground to gnaw on tree roots. The mushrooms on its back absorb most of the nutrition.

47.description: The larger the mushroom on its back grows, the stronger the mushroom spores it scatters.

48.description: Its big eyes are actually clusters of tiny eyes. At night, its kind is drawn by light.

49.description: The wings are covered with dustlike scales. Every time it flaps its wings, it looses highly toxic dust.

50.description: Its skin is very thin. If it is exposed to light, its blood heats up, causing it to grow weak.

51.description: Extremely powerful, they can dig through even the hardest ground to a depth of over 60 miles.

52.description: It is nocturnal in nature. If it spots something shiny, its eyes glitter brightly.

53.description: A very haughty Pokémon. Among fans, the size of the jewel in its forehead is a topic of much talk.

54.description: It has mystical powers but doesn't recall that it has used them. That is why it always looks puzzled.

55.description: The forelegs are webbed, helping to make it an adept swimmer. It can be seen swimming elegantly in lakes, etc.

56.description: It lives in treetop colonies. If one becomes enraged, the whole colony rampages for no reason.

57.description: It is always outrageously furious. If it gives chase, it will tenaciously track the target no matter how far.

58.description: It has a brave and trustworthy nature. It fearlessly stands up to bigger and stronger foes.

59.description: Its magnificent bark conveys a sense of majesty. Anyone hearing it can't help but grovel before it.

60.description: The direction of the spiral on the belly differs by area. It is more adept at swimming than walking.

61.description: Its two legs are well developed. Even though it can live on the ground, it prefers living in water.

62.description: A swimmer adept at both the front crawl and breaststroke. Easily overtakes the best human swimmers.

63.description: It senses impending attacks and teleports away to safety before the actual attacks can strike.

64.description: If it uses its abilities, it emits special alpha waves that cause machines to malfunction.

65.description: Its brain can outperform a supercomputer. Its IQ (intelligence quotient) is said to be around 5,000.

66.description: Its whole body is composed of muscles. Even though it's the size of a human child, it can hurl 100 grown-ups.

67.description: It can lift a dump truck with one hand. Using that power, it helps people with heavy jobs.

68.description: It uses its four powerful arms to pin the limbs of its foe, then throws the victim over the horizon.

69.description: Its bud looks like a human face. Because of the bud, it is rumored to be a type of legendary mandrake plant.

70.description: It spits out Poison Powder to immobilize the enemy and then finishes it with a spray of Acid.

71.description: Once ingested into this Pokémon's body, even the hardest object will melt into nothing.

72.description: Drifts in shallow seas. Anglers who hook them by accident are often punished by their stingers.

73.description: It has 80 tentacles that move about freely. They can sting, causing poisoning and sharp, stabbing pain.

74.description: It is impossible to distinguish from rocks. It slams against others in contests of hardness.

75.description: Rolls down slopes to move. It rolls over any obstacle without slowing or changing its direction.

76.description: Even dynamite can't harm its hard, boulder-like body. It sheds its hide just once a year.

77.description: Its legs grow strong while it chases after its parent. It runs in fields and mountains all day.

78.description: It gallops at nearly 150 mph. With its mane blazing ferociously, it races as if it were an arrow.

79.description: It lazes vacantly near water. If something bites its tail, it won't even notice for a whole day.

80.description: When a Slowpoke went hunting in the sea, its tail was bitten by a Shellder. That made it evolve into Slowbro.

81.description: It moves while constantly hovering. It discharges Thunder Wave and so on from the units at its sides.

82.description: Generates strange radio signals. It raises the temperature by 3.6 degrees Fahrenheit within 3,300 feet.

83.description: It always walks about with a plant stalk clamped in its beak. The stalk is used for building its nest.

84.description: The brains in its two heads appear to communicate emotions to each other with a telepathic power.

85.description: An odd species that is rarely found. The three heads respectively represent joy, sadness, and anger.

86.description: The colder it gets, the better it feels. It joyfully swims around oceans so cold that they are filled with floating ice.

87.description: Its streamlined body has low resistance, and it swims around cold oceans at a speed of eight knots.

88.description: Born from sludge, these Pokémon now gather in polluted places and increase the bacteria in their bodies.

89.description: They love to gather in smelly areas where sludge accumulates, making the stench around them worse.

90.description: Clamping on to an opponent reveals its vulnerable parts, so it uses this move only as a last resort.

91.description: Its shell is extremely hard. It cannot be shattered, even with a bomb. The shell opens only when it is attacking.

92.description: Born from gases, anyone would faint if engulfed by its gaseous body, which contains poison.

93.description: It licks with its gaseous tongue to steal the victim's life force. It lurks in darkness for prey.

94.description: Hiding in people's shadows at night, it absorbs their heat. The chill it causes makes the victims shake.

95.description: It usually lives underground. It searches for food while boring its way through the ground at 50 miles per hour.

96.description: If you think that you had a good dream but you can't remember it, a Drowzee has probably eaten it.

97.description: Seeing its swinging pendulum can induce sleep in three seconds, even in someone who just woke up.

98.description: It can be found near the sea. The large pincers grow back if they are torn out of their sockets.

99.description: Its pincers grow peculiarly large. If it lifts the pincers too fast, it loses its balance and staggers.

100.description: Usually found in power plants. Easily mistaken for a Poké Ball, it has zapped many people.

101.description: It stores an overflowing amount of electric energy inside its body. Even a small shock makes it explode.

102.description: Even though it appears to be eggs of some sort, it was discovered to be a life-form more like plant seeds.

103.description: It is called 'The Walking Jungle.' If a head grows too big, it falls off and becomes an Exeggcute.

104.description: It always wears the skull of its dead mother, so no one has any idea what its hidden face looks like.

105.description: The bone it holds is its key weapon. It throws the bone skillfully like a boomerang to KO targets.

106.description: If it starts kicking repeatedly, both legs will stretch even longer to strike a fleeing foe.

107.description: The arm-twisting punches it throws pulverize even concrete. It rests after three minutes of fighting.

108.description: Its tongue is twice the length of its body. It can be moved like an arm for grabbing food and attacking.

109.description: Toxic gas is held within its thin, balloon-shaped body, so it can cause massive explosions.

110.description: Inhaling toxic fumes from trash and mixing them inside its body lets it spread an even fouler stench.

111.description: It is inept at turning because of its four short legs. It can only charge and run in one direction.

112.description: It begins walking on its hind legs after evolution. It can punch holes through boulders with its horn.

113.description: It lays several eggs in a day. The eggs are apparently rich in nutrients and extremely delicious.

114.description: It tangles any moving thing with its vines. Their subtle shaking is ticklish if you get ensnared.

115.description: If it is safe, the young gets out of the belly pouch to play. The adult keeps a close eye on the youngster.

116.description: It makes its nest in the shade of corals. If it senses danger, it spits murky ink and flees.

117.description: It is capable of swimming backwards by rapidly flapping its winglike pectoral fins and stout tail.

118.description: Its dorsal, pectoral, and tail fins wave elegantly in water. That is why it is known as the water dancer.

119.description: It makes its nest by hollowing out boulders in streams with its horn. It defends its eggs with its life.

120.description: It appears in large numbers by seashores. At night, its central core flashes with a red light.

121.description: At the center of its body is a red core, which sends mysterious radio signals into the night sky.

122.description: It is adept at conning people. It is said to be able to create walls out of thin air by miming.

123.description: It slashes through grass with its sharp scythes, moving too fast for the human eye to track.

124.description: It speaks using a language that sounds human. Research is under way to determine what is being said.

125.description: It loves to feed on strong electricity. It occassionally appears around large power plants and so on.

126.description: Found near the mouth of a volcano. This fire-breather's body temperature is nearly 2,200 degree Fahrenheit.

127.description: It swings its long pincer horns wildly to attack. During cold periods, it hides deep in forests.

128.description: When it is about to tackle, it whips its body repeatedly with its three long tails.

129.description: In the distant past, it was somewhat stronger than the horribly weak descendants that exist today.

130.description: Rarely seen in the wild. Huge and vicious, it is capable of destroying entire cities in a rage.

131.description: Its high intelligence enables it to understand human speech. It likes to ferry people on its back.

132.description: It can freely recombine its own cellular structure to transform into other life-forms.

133.description: Thanks to its unstable genetic makeup, this special Pokémon conceals many different possible evolutions.

134.description: It has evolved to be suitable for an aquatic life. It can invisibly melt away into water.

135.description: It accumulates negative ions in the atmosphere to blast out 10,000-volt lightning bolts.

136.description: It has a flame bag inside its body. After inhaling deeply, it blows out flames of nearly 3,000 degrees Fahrenheit.

137.description: A man-made Pokémon created using advanced scientific means. It can move freely in cyberspace.

138.description: Revived from an ancient fossil, this Pokémon uses air stored in its shell to sink and rise int water.

139.description: Its tentacles are highly developed as if they are hands and feet. As soon as it ensnares prey, it bites.

140.description: This Pokémon was regenerated from the fossil of an ancient creature. It protects itself with a hard shell.

141.description: In the water, it tucks in its limbs to become more compact, then it wiggles its shell to swim fast.

142.description: This vicious Pokémon is said to have flown in ancient skies while shrieking high-pitched cries.

143.description: Its stomach can digest any kind of food, even if it happens to be moldy or rotten.

144.description: A legendary bird Pokémon. It can create blizzards by freezing moisture in the air.

145.description: A legendary Pokémon that is said to live in thunderclouds. It freely controls lightning bolts.

146.description: One of the legendary bird Pokémon. It is said that its appearance indicates the coming of spring.

147.description: This Pokémon is full of life energy. It continually sheds its skin and grows steadily larger.

148.description: A mystical Pokémon that exudes a gentle aura. It is said to have the ability to change the weather.

149.description: It is said to make its home somewhere in the sea. It guides crews of shipwrecks to shore.

150.description: A Pokémon created by recombining Mew's genes. It's said to have the most savage heart among Pokémon.

151.description: Because it can use all kinds of moves, many scientists believe Mew to be the ancestor of Pokémon.

172.description: Despite its small size, it can zap even adult humans. However, if it does so, it also surprises itself.

173.description: When numerous meteors illuminate the night sky, sightings of Cleffa strangely increase.

174.description: Its extremely flexible and elastic body makes it bounce continuously - anytime, anywhere.

175.description: A proverb claims that happiness will come to anyone who can make a sleeping Togepi stand up.

176.description: It grows dispirited if it is not with kind people. It can float in midair without moving its wings.

238.description: It always rocks its head slowly backwards and forwards as if it is trying to kiss someone.

239.description: Even in the most vicious storm, this Pokemon plays happily if thunder rumbles in the sky.

240.description: It is found in volcanic craters. Its body heat exceeds 1,100 degrees F, so don't underestimate it.
